attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a DDoS flooder bot. Its main attack function, `sub_80488d0`, contains the string `"[http flood] headers: \"%s\"\\n"`, explicitly identifying its purpose. The malware daemonizes itself by forking and redirecting standard I/O streams to `/dev/null` (seen in `sub_805296d` and `sub_80528f9`). It then establishes a connection to a Command and Control (C2) server, receives attack parameters (e.g., parsing `url=`), and proceeds to launch an HTTP flood attack by sending a high volume of crafted HTTP requests to the specified target.
